<bibRefCitation author="Radoszkowski, O" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of Zoological Nomenclature" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" refId="B25" refString="Radoszkowski, O, 1877. Chrysidiformes, Mutillidae et Sphegidae. In: Fedtshenko AP (Ed.) Putieshestvie v Turkestan [Voyage au Turkestan d'Alexis Fedtschenko] (14) 2(5), Sankt- Petersburg, 1-87. [+ 8 pls] [In Russian and Latin]" title="Chrysidiformes, Mutillidae et Sphegidae. In: Fedtshenko AP (Ed.) Putieshestvie v Turkestan [Voyage au Turkestan d'Alexis Fedtschenko] (14) 2 (5), Sankt- Petersburg, 1 - 87. [+ 8 pls] [In Russian and Latin]" year="1877">Radoszkowski 1877</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Mocsary, A" journalOrPublisher="Hungarian Academy of Science, Budapest" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" refId="B22" refString="Mocsary, A, 1889. Monographia Chrysididarum Orbis Terrarum Universi. Hungarian Academy of Science, Budapest" title="Monographia Chrysididarum Orbis Terrarum Universi." year="1889">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Mocsáry">Mocsary</normalizedToken>
1889
</bibRefCitation>
; du Buysson in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="André">Andre</normalizedToken>
1896; Kimsey and Bohart 1991).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="149" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="149">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="149">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Radoszkowski" authorityYear="1877" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chrysis speciosa" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speciosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">Chrysis speciosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Radoszkowski, 1877 is a member of the 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. maculicornis" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" rank="species" species="maculicornis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">C. maculicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group and it is recognised by the colour pattern with body fully metallic blue; first and second flagellum short; flagellomeres extensively yellowish and tarsi yellow; metasoma with large, deep and even punctures (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Chrysis speciosa Radoszkowski, male A head, frontal view B habitus, dorsal view C genital capsule D habitus, lateral view E metasoma, posterior view F metasoma, postero-lateral view G metasoma, ventral view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1068.73549.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/608670" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">3E</figureCitation>
); post pit row area on T3 wide; apical teeth on T3 elongate (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Chrysis speciosa Radoszkowski, male A head, frontal view B habitus, dorsal view C genital capsule D habitus, lateral view E metasoma, posterior view F metasoma, postero-lateral view G metasoma, ventral view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1068.73549.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/608670" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">3D and F</figureCitation>
), with apex non-metallic brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Chrysis speciosa Radoszkowski, male A head, frontal view B habitus, dorsal view C genital capsule D habitus, lateral view E metasoma, posterior view F metasoma, postero-lateral view G metasoma, ventral view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1068.73549.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/608670" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">3E and F</figureCitation>
); black spots on S2 large and subrectangular (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Chrysis speciosa Radoszkowski, male A head, frontal view B habitus, dorsal view C genital capsule D habitus, lateral view E metasoma, posterior view F metasoma, postero-lateral view G metasoma, ventral view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1068.73549.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/608670" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">3G</figureCitation>
). Only two species with blue males are known in this group, 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. tatianae" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" rank="species" species="tatianae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">C. tatianae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Semenov-Tian-Shanskij, 1967 and 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. kokomerenica" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" rank="species" species="kokomerenica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">C. kokomerenica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Tarbinsky, 2002, both separated from 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. speciosa" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" rank="species" species="speciosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">C. speciosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by flagellomeres fully black.
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/zookeys.1068.73549.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/608670" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" start="Figure 3" startId="F3">
